ğŸ§  Core Logic (Say this FIRST in interview)

â€œI split the sentence into words using space as delimiter.
Then I store each word and its frequency in a HashMap.â€

ğŸ“Œ Why HashMap?
Fast lookup and clean frequency counting.

import java.util.*;

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String sentence = "java is easy and java is powerful";
        Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        // Step 1: Split sentence into words
        String[] words = sentence.split(" ");

        // Step 2: Count frequency of each word
        for (String word : words) {
            map.put(word, map.getOrDefault(word, 0) + 1);
        }

        // Step 3: Print word frequencies
        for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> entry : map.entrySet()) {
            System.out.println(entry.getKey() + " = " + entry.getValue());
        }
    }
}



